sql:
SELECT property_id
FROM chemical_properties
ORDER BY property_id, created_at;

SELECT AVG(value) AS average_value
FROM chemical_properties
WHERE type_id = (SELECT type_id FROM property_types WHERE type_name = 'pH');

SELECT type_name
FROM property_types
ORDER BY type_name ASC;

SELECT value 
FROM chemical_properties 
ORDER BY value DESC;

external_knowledge:
- 'architects of chemical properties' refers to the names of property types (type_name); 
- 'masterplans' refers to the values of the chemical properties (value);
- 'more than a decade of experience' refers to having more than 10 entries for each property type (COUNT(cp.property_id) > 10).

sql:
SELECT value, created_at
FROM chemical_properties
ORDER BY created_at DESC;
